ass=\"nova-legacy-e-badge nova-legacy-e-badge--color-green nova-legacy-e-badge--display-block nova-legacy-e-badge--luminosity-medium nova-legacy-e-badge--size-l nova-legacy-e-badge--theme-ghost nova-legacy-e-badge--radius-m nova-legacy-v-publication-item__fulltext\">Full-text available</span></div><div class=\"nova-legacy-v-publication-item__meta-right\"><ul class=\"nova-legacy-e-list nova-legacy-e-list--size-m nova-legacy-e-list--type-inline nova-legacy-e-list--spacing-none nova-legacy-v-publication-item__meta-data\"><li class=\"nova-legacy-e-list__item nova-legacy-v-publication-item__meta-data-item\"><span class=\"\">Oct 2010</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div class=\"nova-legacy-v-publication-item__stack-item\"><ul class=\"nova-legacy-e-list nova-legacy-e-list--size-m nova-legacy-e-list--type-inline nova-legacy-e-list--spacing-none nova-legacy-v-publication-item__person-list\"><li class=\"nova-legacy-e-list__item\"><a class=\"nova-legacy-e-link nova-legacy-e-link--color-inherit nova-legacy-e-link--theme-bare\" href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Shamal-Faily\"><span class=\"nova-legacy-v-person-inline-item\"><span class=\"lite-person-inline-item__image\"><picture class=\"lite-page-avatar lite-page-avatar--size-xs lite-page-avatar--radius-full\"> <img src=\"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAYAAAAfFcSJAAAADUlEQVR42mN89OjNfwAJDwOxHEacwgAAAABJRU5ErkJggg==\" data-src=\"https://i1.rgstatic.net/ii/profile.image/277697470189574-1443219644366_Q64/Shamal-Faily.jpg\" class=\"lite-image\" alt=\"Shamal Faily\"/></picture></span><span class=\"nova-legacy-v-person-inline-item__fullname\">Shamal Faily</span></span></a></li><li class=\"nova-legacy-e-list__item\"><a class=\"nova-legacy-e-link nova-legacy-e-link--color-inherit nova-legacy-e-link--theme-bare\" href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/scientific-contributions/Ivan-Flechais-70175264\"><span class=\"nova-legacy-v-person-inline-item\"><span class=\"nova-legacy-v-person-inline-item__fullname\">Ivan Flechais</span></span></a></li></ul></div><div class=\"nova-legacy-v-publication-item__stack-item\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-e-text nova-legacy-e-text--size-m nova-legacy-e-text--family-sans-serif nova-legacy-e-text--spacing-none nova-legacy-e-text--color-inherit nova-legacy-e-text--clamp-3 nova-legacy-v-publication-item__description\"><span class=\"js-target-abstract-61a683676f66a lite-page-hidden\">Personas are useful for obtaining an empirically grounded understanding of a secure system&#x27;s user population, its contexts of use, and possible vulnerabilities and threats endangering it. Often, however, personas need to be partially derived from assumptions; these may be embedded in a variety of dierent representations. Assumption Personas have been proposed as boundary objects for articulating assumptions about a user population, but no methods or tools currently exist for developing and rening these within the context of secure and usable design. This paper presents an approach for developing and rening as- sumption personas before and during the design of secure systems. We present a model for structuring the contribution of assumptions to as- sumption personas, together with a process for developing assumption personas founded on this model. We also present some preliminary re- sults based on an application of this approach in a recent case study.</span></div></div></div></div><footer class=\"nova-legacy-v-publication-item__footer\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-v-publication-item__footer-actions\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-o-pack nova-legacy-o-pack--gutter-m nova-legacy-o-pack--width-auto nova-legacy-o-pack--vertical-align-middle\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-o-pack__item nova-legacy-v-publication-item__footer-button-group\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-c-button-group nova-legacy-c-button-group--gutter-m nova-legacy-c-button-group--orientation-horizontal nova-legacy-c-button-group--width-auto nova-legacy-v-publication-item__actions\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-c-button-group__item\"><a class=\"nova-legacy-c-button nova-legacy-c-button--align-center nova-legacy-c-button--radius-m nova-legacy-c-button--size-s nova-legacy-c-button--color-blue nova-legacy-c-button--theme-bare nova-legacy-c-button--width-auto nova-legacy-v-publication-item__action\" href=\"publication/221045854_The_Secret_Lives_of_Assumptions_Developing_and_Refining_Assumption_Personas_for_Secure_System_Design\"><span class=\"nova-legacy-c-button__label\">View</span></a></div><div class=\"nova-legacy-c-button-group__item\"><button class=\"nova-legacy-c-button nova-legacy-c-button--align-center nova-legacy-c-button--radius-m nova-legacy-c-button--size-s nova-legacy-c-button--color-blue nova-legacy-c-button--theme-bare nova-legacy-c-button--width-auto nova-legacy-v-publication-item__action\" type=\"button\"><span class=\"nova-legacy-c-button__label\"><span class=\" js-lite-click\" data-lite=\"{&quot;click&quot;:[{&quot;t&quot;:&quot;.js-target-abstract-61a683676f66a&quot;,&quot;a&quot;:&quot;tc(lite-page-hidden)&quot;},{&quot;t&quot;:&quot;self&quot;,&quot;a&quot;:&quot;tc(lite-page-hidden)&quot;}]}\">Show abstract</span></span></button></div></div></div></div></div></footer></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"nova-legacy-o-stack__item publication-citations__item publication-citations__item--redesign\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-v-citation-item\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-o-stack nova-legacy-o-stack--gutter-m nova-legacy-o-stack--spacing-none nova-legacy-o-stack--no-gutter-outside\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-o-stack__item\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-v-citation-item__context-source\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-v-publication-item nova-legacy-v-publication-item--size-m gtm-reference-item\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-v-publication-item__body\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-v-publication-item__stack nova-legacy-v-publication-item__stack--gutter-m\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-v-publication-item__stack-item\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-e-text nova-legacy-e-text--size-l nova-legac